HEADWORD: Self-confidence
<hw>Self`-con"fi*dence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality
or state of being self-confident; self-reliance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A feeling of <qex>self-confidence</qex> which supported and
sustained him.</q> <rj><qau>Beaconsfield.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-confident</ent>⟦br⟧
